    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Chemistry              : Modern spectroscopic techniques for structure determination. The chemistry of alcohols, ethers, carbonyl compounds, and amines, with special attention to mechanistic aspects. Special topics.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Michel Daoust, Mitchell Huot, Laura Pavelka, Dmytro Perepichka, David Noble Harpp (Fall)                  Michel Daoust, Mitchell Huot, Laura Pavelka, Karine Auclair (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall, Winter</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: CHEM 212 or equivalent.</li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken an equivalent Organic 2 at CEGEP (see McGill University Basic Math and Sciences Equivalence Table at <a href="http://www.mcgill.ca/mathscitable" title="www.mcgill.ca/mathscitable" rel="nofollow">www.mcgill.ca/mathscitable</a>) or who have or are taking CHEM 234.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

