                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/chem-381" class="program-course-title">
              CHEM 381 Inorganic Chemistry 2 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-20414" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Chemistry (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Chemistry              : Introduction to transition metal chemistry, coordination numbers and geometry, and nomenclature will be followed by a discussion of crystal field theory and its applications to problems in spectroscopy, magnetochemistry, thermodynamics and kinetics. Several aspects related to applications of organometallic compounds in catalysis and bioinorganic systems will be discussed.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        David Bohle (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: CHEM 281.</li>
              <li>Restriction: For Honours and Major Chemistry students</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

